<body class="ignore-math">
<h3 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h3>
<p>With this place, we will introduce some notation.  The notation is motivated by the fact that integration (putting together, summing) is the inverse process of differentiation (taking a difference).  With this in mind, the integral of a differential <span class="process-math">\(\dx{y}\)</span> is denoted by</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\int\dx{y}\text{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-1.html#p-10" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
</body>
